The paper deals with designing randomized mechanisms for customers to reserve instances in cloud computing, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.DS). The mechanisms are designed to optimize social welfare and providers' revenue, which falls under distributed computing (cs.DC) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions value density, which is a concept from information theory (cs.IT).
